    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Great Valley</b> (262Aq). Stands occur at the Monocline Ridge area of western Fresno Co. on convex, undulating sand dunes in small patches adjacent to <i>Ephedra californica</i> stands and other grassland types (Evens et al. 2006).</li>
        
            <li><b>Mojave Desert</b> (322Ai). Stands occur in sandy areas such as the Devilâ€™s Playground.</li>
        
            <li><b>Northwestern Basin and Range</b> (342Ba, Be). Stands occur on the Madeline Plain north of Honey Lake and in Surprise Valley (CVIS 2007).</li>
        
            <li><b>Sierra Nevada</b> (M261Ek). Stands are found on rocky ridges at alpine elevations near Carson Pass (Major and Taylor 1977).</li>
        
            <li><b>Southeastern Great Basin</b> (341Fb-c, Fe). Stands are found at the Eureka Dunes (Thomas et al. 2004) and adjacent areas in the Coso and Inyo mountains.</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> The alliance is very rare in California, and we need more inventorying and monitoring of stands that occur in the state. <i>Achnatherum hymenoides </i>is forage for livestock, but areas are easily depleted by heavy, early spring grazing. It is useful in restoration projects in desert areas disturbed by construction activity, fire, heavy grazing, and surface mining (Tirmenstein 1999a). </div>
</div>

    

    

    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Associations</h4>
        
            
